title: Living Cultures Collection 13of13 The Young Girl and the Monkey
description: Living Cultures: Collection Culture Documentary hosted by Paul Bandey, published by ZED in 2012 - English narration http://docuwiki.net/images/8/85/Living-Cultures-Collection-Cover.jpg Information ------------------------------ Living Cultures: Collection 13) The Young Girl and the Monkey (Cambodia) Sokhun was once a famous dancer in Cambodia, but when the Khmer Rouge took over the country, all that came to an end. When a Khmer Rouge asked her what she did, she said she was a seamstress - but at night she went over the songs and dances in her head. Now, she teaches dance.
